Defendant Jennifer L Parr in court with attorney Mary D Scholle.  Defendant Jennifer L Parr in custody.  Randy P Sitzberger appeared for the State of Wisconsin./ SAB
  Sentencing Proceeded. Statements by the State, defense counsel and defendant. 
The Court sentenced defendant to serve a term of IMPRISONMENT in the Wisconsin State Prisons for 36 MONTHS.  INITIAL CONFINEMENT of 18 MONTHS and EXTENDED SUPERVISION of 18 MONTHS, consecutive to any other sentence, credit for 108 days.
Defendant is eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and is eligible for the Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program.
-Restitution in the amount of $559.67 is to be paid to Marilyn F-C.  from up to 25% of prison funds, balance to be paid by 5/6/2017; nonpayment penalty shall be a civil judgment. Restitution is to be paid BEFORE court costs.
-Court costs and victim/witness surcharges are to be paid from up to 25% of prison funds, balance to be paid by 5/6/2017; nonpayment penalty shall be a civil judgment.
-Defendant is to provide a DNA sample and pay the related surcharge from up to 25% of prison funds, balance to be paid by 5/6/2017; nonpayment penalty shall be a civil judgment.
CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:
-AODA assessment and any recommended treatment
-Absolute sobriety with random urine screens and breathalyzers
-No alcohol or controlled substances
-Mental health assessment and any recommended treatment to include any couseling, therapy and taking any prescribed medications
-Employment or school
-Successfully complete a Cognitive Thinking Behavioral Modification Program
-Successfully complete a Parenting Program
Court advised the defendant that as a convicted felon she may no longer use or possess any firearms or body armor; also she may not vote in any election until her civil rights have been restored.

Defendant Jennifer L Parr in court with attorney Mary D. Scholle.  Defendant Jennifer L Parr in custody.  Randy P. Sitzberger appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
  Deputy Court Clerk:  ss

  Defendant changes his plea to GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional Rights and the maximum penalty.  Court found that defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights.  Plea questionnaire received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea.  Court found defendant guilty as charged in the Information and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.  Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon he may not possess any firearms. No voting until civil rights are restored.  No possession of body armor.

Parties stipulate to restitution in the amount of $559.67.  Payment conditions to be addressed at sentencing.

  Court ordered case adjourned for sentencing in Branch 15  Sentencing hearing scheduled for 05-06-2014 at 01:30 pm.
